Shiny Application and Reproducible Pitch

As part of the course Developing Data Products from Johns Hopkins University.

Introduction

Those slides present a Shiny application available at http://benjamin-berhault.shinyapps.io/FDNY

This ShinyApp allows you to visualise Emergency Response Incidents in New York City based on data from the NYC OpenData portal for the period 2013 to 2015.

Original inspiration by David Kahle

CrimeMap

Explanation

To smooth data due to major differences in data amount between categories, I use the hyperbolic tangent function

custom_tanh <- function(x){tanh(2*x)}

on the alpha scale calibration parameter of the stat_density2d() function.

scale_alpha(range = c(0, custom_tanh(nrow(create.df())/max(incident_occurences)))
